"Xinhua All Media Plus | Beijing Youth Ice Hockey League ignites Winter Olympics passion - Xinhua News Agency"
"On December 11th, Beijing Dreaming ING team player Pang Yaotian (middle) shoots during the game."
"On the same day, the 2021-2022 season of the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League continued to compete in major ice rinks in Beijing."
"This league is divided into regular season and playoffs, with participating athletes aged from U6 to U18. The categories are divided into competitive and selection groups, attracting nearly 3600 players from 256 representative teams in the city."
"After over ten years of development, the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League has become a platform for Beijing youth ice hockey enthusiasts to sharpen their skills and make friends, and it delivers outstanding players to Beijing youth and young teams."
"The league plays a leading role in promoting youth ice hockey in Beijing, igniting enthusiasm for ice hockey in the Winter Olympics, and laying the foundation for the development of ice hockey in Beijing in the post-Winter Olympics period."